An update from the team‚Ä¶
 
Alex is now back in the UK with his family, where he‚Äôll spend Christmas.
 
HUGO BOSS, meanwhile, will remain in Cape Town (she‚Äôs in good company, @sebastien.simon üòâ ) until the New Year.
 
In January, Alex and the crew plan to return to Cape Town, replace the rudder and sail the boat back to the UK.
 
A big thank you from the whole team for all your messages of support. We‚Äôve said it before and we‚Äôll say it again‚Ä¶.we have the best fans in the world!
 
To the rest of the @vendeeglobe2020 skippers, fair winds and keep on pushing!

Image may contain: text that says 'THE INCIDENT OCCURRED ON WHAT WAS THOMSON'S 19TH DAY OF RACING IN THE ROUND-THE-WORLD VEND√âE GLOBE YACHT RACE, WHICH BEGAN ON SUNDAY 8TH NOVEMBER FROM LES SABLES- D'OLONNE ON FRANCE'S WEST COAST. ALEX THOMSON IS CURRENTLY APPROXIMATELY ,800NAUTICAL MILES FROM CAPE TOWN IS EXPECTED TO TAKE THE SKIPPER AROUND SEVEN DAYS TO MAKE THE JOURNEY.
